# Atlas realtime avatar (talk in browser)

When the user asks to **talk to their avatar**, **Atlas realtime**, **passthrough avatar**, or similar:

**OpenClaw:** Send users to **[https://docs.openclaw.ai/install](https://docs.openclaw.ai/install)** for install, update, verify, and uninstall. Do not pin OpenClaw versions or duplicate install commands in chat.

1. **Secrets:** Use **`ATLAS_API_KEY`** (and optional **`ATLAS_API_BASE`**) from the project **`.env`** or OpenClaw env. Never paste keys into chat.
2. **Bootstrap UI** (from repo root):  
   `bash skills/atlas-avatar/scripts/setup-realtime-viewer.sh`  
   Override install dir with **`ATLAS_REALTIME_VIEWER_DIR`** if needed. Re-run after changing env so **`.env.local`** picks up **`LLM_*`** / **`ELEVENLABS_*`** when those vars are exported.
3. **Run the app:** `cd` to that directory, **`npm run dev`**. If port 3000 is busy, Next may use **3001** — read the terminal line **`Local:`** and open that URL.
4. **User action:** They open the app in a **real browser**, click **Connect**, allow **microphone** if prompted. WebRTC does not run inside the chat panel.
5. **Optional CLI session:** `python3 skills/atlas-avatar/scripts/atlas_session.py start --face-url …` then send them **`http://localhost:<port>/watch/<session_id>`** with the same API key.
6. **Billing:** Remind them to **Disconnect** / **`leave`** when done.

If the UI shows **“LLM + TTS not configured”**, the example app needs **`LLM_API_KEY`** (and related **`LLM_*`**) plus **`ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`** in **`.env.local`** — export them in the shell before re-running the setup script, or edit **`.env.local`** manually (do not commit).
